other_tests.findings: No exposed blood vessels or granulation tissue in the trachea or stoma.

Histopathological examination revealed an abscess with purulent inflammation surrounded by granulomatous inflammation and fibrosis; Identification of a sulfur granule and filamentous structures typical of Actinomyces species.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The culture of the tissue and abscess specimens grew A. israelii and Aggregatibacter actinomycetemcomitans.
